main event: Radar detection of two unidentified airborne objects over the Atlantic Ocean on October 31, 1960
interesting points: The objects passed approximately 30-35 nautical miles south of the observer's location.
The objects were tracked on radar for about 1 minute.
The objects were traveling at a speed of approximately 3,962 knots (over 4,500 mph).
The report suggests the objects could have been a mirage or due to atmospheric conditions.
The location of the sighting was reported as latitude 19°48'N, longitude 73°40'W.
sighted object: two unidentified airborne objects detected on radar
photographs: no photographs included in the report
